    "body": "I can work on this if this feature is still being considered.\r\n\r\nMy current thought is as following:\r\n1. do a regex match `r\"^v?\\d+(\\.\\d+)*$\"` on `dep.tag` before `git checkout` ([here](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/37452a3644e6a7e356204096232345f8aede53b6/cli/src/cmd/forge/install.rs#L143) and [here](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/37452a3644e6a7e356204096232345f8aede53b6/cli/src/cmd/forge/install.rs#L199))\r\n2. if there's a match, we get the list of tags in the repo with `git tag`\r\n3. show the list of matching tags and let user select which one to use.\r\n\r\nThis should improve the UX when specifying a version tag, while the functionality of selecting a branches/commits to install still stays the same.",
