    "body": "Given the above observation, I would like to suggest that we revamp the install process as follow:\r\n1. Always clone/add the repo as submodule **without checking the tag**. Because I think the intention is clear that the user want to install the repo, even if they supply an invalid tag.\r\n2. Give the user a chance to disambiguate the tag if it \"looks like\" a version tag. (We may do similar UX improvement for other kinds of tags in the future if wanted.)\r\n>     1. do a regex match `r\"^v?\\d+(\\.\\d+)*$\"` on `dep.tag`.\r\n>     2. if there's a match, we get the list of tags in the repo with `git tag`.\r\n>     3. show the list of candidate tags and let user select which one to use.\r\n3. After that, if the tag is still invalid, i.e. `git checkout tag` fail, then we show a clear warning and suggest actions to take.",
